data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**Sync I/O on the Cosmos DB provider is fully removed.** In .NET 10 you could opt in to sync-over-async; in EF Core 11, all synchronous calls (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`, etc.) **always throw** ã no opt-in exists.

Every method in your repository must become `async`:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
- Return `Task<T>` / `Task`, mark methods `async`
- `ToList()` ã `await ToListAsync()`
- `First()` ã `await FirstAsync()`
- `Count()` ã `await CountAsync()`
- `SaveChanges()` ã `await SaveChangesAsync()`

All callers up the chain must also be updated to `await` these methods. There is no workaround ã the Cosmos SDK is async-only, and EF Core 11 no longer bridges sync over async.
